      "content": "that makes sense for the systemic side, but some people argue that we shouldn't just look at the police or poverty. they argue that even when you control for those things, there are still differences in crime rates between groups. if you were looking at the actual data from a purely statistical or even biological standpoint, what would lead to those disparities?",
